# QA MODE: POST-BUILD SEMANTIC REVIEW

> **TL;DR:** The `/qa` command performs a structured semantic review of code implemented during BUILD mode against the original plan. It runs *after* BUILD (not before), catches over-engineering, incomplete implementations, pattern violations, and implementation debris. Required for L2+ tasks; gates `/reflect`. It also performs universal validation (Memory Bank consistency, task tracking, reference checks) as part of its review.

